HEADWORD: Ruthenic
<hw>Ru*then"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or containing, ruthenium; specifically, designating
those compounds in which it has a higher valence as contrasted with
<contr>ruthenious</contr> compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ruthenious</ent>⟦br⟧
